result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Donquil D McLemore

records.addlTxt: Notice of Court Order to Jefferson County Dispatch
Initial appearance on November 7, 2022 at 09:00 am.

[MK] case called at 9:25am 
Defendant Donquil D McLemore appears by video-conference from the Dane County Jail, in custody.  ADA Jeffrey Shock in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
The Court finds the Zoom video-connection to be sight and sound sufficient.  

The Court quashes the Warrant.  

This case is also scheduled for Initial Appearance today, however Mr. McLemore indicates that he has not received a copy of the Criminal Complaint. 
Right to counsel is reviewed.  Mr. McLemore indicates that he wishes to have counsel. The Court requires Mr. McLemore to telephone the Jefferson Public Defenders Office by 12:00pm tomorrow; the telephone number is recited. 
The Court requires a $500 Cash Bond.   
recess 9:30am 

NEXT:  (1)  clerk- email the Jefferson PD Office to inform them that Mr. McLemore wishes to have counsel so they should mail the PD application paperwork to him at the Dane County Jail,  (2) Initial Appearance (and status of counsel hearing) on November 7th at 9:00am--arrangements should be made for Mr. McLemore to appear by video ; JA- when NOH is mailed to Mr. McLemore at the Dane County Jail, please include a printed copy of the Criminal Complaint in that mailing
Voluntary appearance/Initial appearance on October 24, 2022 at 09:30 am.
Reasons: Defendant failed to report to jail. Warrant also eady exists for defendant in Dane County case 21CF2592.
